CIG Pannonia Eletbiztosito Nyrt., a
Hungarian life insurer, headed for the biggest decline in more
than four months.  The shares weakened 6.3 percent to 435 forint by 10:41 a.m.
in Budapest, the biggest drop on a closing basis since November.
The slump almost reversed a 6.7 percent rally on March 23.  To contact the reporter on this story:
